What is the relevance of value proposition in a business model? What are the elements of a business model? Explain.

Ans.
Value proposition in a business model is a promise made by a business to its customers which explains what makes the companyâ€™s products or services worth choosing. It basically explains it to customers the gains the customers will make when they buy that specific product and how it is different or/and better than the competition. There are various features of value proposition which are -
a. Value propositions help in attracting and retaining customers by showing them the advantages of the product or service they are providing.

b. Value proposition helps a brand stand out in the crowded market by showing how their products are unique and better than their competition.

c. Value proposition builds a positive image of the brand which in turn helps in influencing the customers about how customers think about their products.

d. Value proposition helps in driving sales and revenue growth by showcasing the value a customer gets when they buy their product.

A business model acts as a blueprint of the company i.e how it creates products that bring value for customers and delivering the value and in return earn money for the services. The main elements of a business model include -
a. The unique solutions provided to a customer.

b. The different groups of people that is being served based on how they are segregated.

c. The various ways the products reach the customers that can be online store and apps etc are managed by channels.

d. Maintaining connections with customers thereby strengthening their relationship.

e. Managing and tracking expenses, income, sales and commissions etc.

f. Managing important business tasks like production, marketing or logistics etc.

g. Improving efficiency and scale of the business by collaborating with partners and suppliers.

h. Tracking the overall cost involved in running the business.
